1) install BSP
     - put released rootfs/uImage to TFTP_DIRECTORY

     you can change above PATH by
      - modify TFTP_FILE
      - modify DHCP_FILE

2) modify DHCP_FILE

     check and modify...

         ------ DHCP_FILE ------------
         option root-path "xxxx/my-rootfs";
                                ~~~~~~~~~
         filename "my-uImage";
                   ~~~~~~~~~
         host xxxx { hardware ethernet 00:xx:yy:zz:aa:bb; }
              ~~~~                     ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
         ------------------------------

3) Put TOP/UBUNTU/start_bsp and stop_bsp
   on your favorite place.

   If you want to start BSP board
     - remove global LAN from eth0
     - set local LAN to eth0
     - run start_bsp

   If you want to stop BSP board
     - remove local LAN from eth0
     - set global LAN to eth0 (if needed)
     - run stop_bsp


you can re-check your work in
  TOP/UBUNTU/comment.log"
